channel.title: Comments on: Local Natives @ The Echo 12.22.09 (Los Angeles, CA)

item.title: By: Jeey
item.dc:creator: Jeey
item.description: Local Natives were ok very likeable but I was a lot more impressed by the songs of Voxhaul Broadcast and their more intense performance.
item.content:encoded: Local Natives were ok very likeable but I was a lot more impressed by the songs of Voxhaul Broadcast and their more intense performance.

item.title: By: Janna
item.dc:creator: Janna
item.description: I went to see what everyone is talking about with Local Natives & Voxhaul Broadcast. I too liked the bass player style for LN but other than a few harmonizing tunes I wasn't impressed. I did like the new tunes from VB and like many others is expecting big things from Voxhaul in 2010.
item.content:encoded: I went to see what everyone is talking about with Local Natives & Voxhaul Broadcast. I did like the new tunes from VB and like many others is expecting big things from Voxhaul in 2010.

item.title: By: jim
item.dc:creator: jim
item.description: I found Local Natives to be a bit boring and the front guys looking more like 70's tv shows like Grizzy Adams & Chips. I did enjoy the opener Voxhaul Broadcast reminds me of earily Nirvana before they got big.
